Former head of the Hawks in Gauteng Shadrack Sibiya was appointment as head of the city&#8217;s internal investigations unit. JOHANNESBURG - Joburg Mayor Herman Mashaba says the anti-corruption unit headed by Shadrack Sibiya will try to recover stolen public money by corrupt government officials.Sibiya's appointment as head of the city s internal investigations unit was announced earlier today.Sibiya was formerly head of the Hawks in Gauteng.Mashaba says the unit will operate independently of any political interference.He says that the unit will bring an end to jobs for friends, stealing of public funds and manipulation of our system. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)